column1: co.easy4u.writer () () () () () () () (Welcome to Writer Plus) () () () () () () () () () (# Writer Plus Welcome to Writer Plus! This file will guide you through some of Writer Plus's features
column2: and give you an introduction to the philosophy behind it.  ## Why did I develop the app? James McMinn's Writer is one of my favorite writing tools
column3: but it is buggy and hasn't been upgraded for 4 years. So I decided to develop an enhanced app following it's philosophy
column4: and to keep on improving it according to users' reviews.  ## What is the "philosophy" that I mean? KEEP IT SIMPLE: That is the idea and philosophy behind Writer Plus. Writing should not be about the tools that you use
column5: but about the ideas and thoughts that you have. Writer Plus aims to give you a simple and enjoyable method to pour your ideas into a text.  ## What are the new features?   - Android Material Design   - Folder (Long press the "+" button)   - Undo & Redo   - Style: Font
column6: Night Mode   - Share   - And many more...  ## Where are my files located? Files are stored in sdcard://Writer/. The documents can be backed up or synced with your Google Drive account
column7: with [Writer Sync](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=co.easy4u.writer.sync).  ## Give it some character Sometimes plain text just doesn't feels right. Writer Plus supports basic [Markdown](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown). That means that you can add *emphasis* or **make a bold statement** in such a simple way.  *A full list of supported markdowns are listed at the end of this document.*  # Happy Writing If you enjoy using Writer Plus
column8: have a request
column9: found a bug
column10: or simply want to contact the developer
column11: then I'd love to hear it from you. Feel free to contact me via email: support@writer.plus.  If you have found it useful
column12: then please give it a high rating on the Android market. :D  # Markdown  # Header 1 ## Header 2 ### Header 3 You can do ~~Scratch~~
column14: **bold** or even ***both***!   + Writer does lists too!   + Weee!   - They can start with a + or a -   - I like the dashes more.  1. Numbered lists too!  2. Lots of lists   > Writer also supports quotes.   > But don't quote me on that. )

column1: com.iggnovation.hackanyone () () () () () () (Being original) (In the analogy with music
column2: we said that you eventually need to learn how to recombine musical patterns (which you have learned by listening to music and practicing performance) into original compositions.) (I chose that way of describing creativity carefully
column3: because it applies to software even more than it does to music.) (Before you have read and absorbed the lessons of a lot of code
column4: you will probably not have in your head the pattern library you need to be creative on scales larger than very small ones.) (One purpose of doing the incremental-hacking cycle is to immerse yourself in a lot of code — at increasing complexity scales — under circumstances that provide you with motivation to keep reading.) (Eventually you will lead group projects and do entirely original work.) (Do not feel you have to rush this or force it; if you give your skills time to mature
column5: your first original composition will be better for it. ) (By contributing effectively to existing open-source projects you will learn the skills (including the communications skills) that you need to run your own projects.) (It is certainly possible to hack things other than software
column6: and people in the maker culture do it. But the term “hacking” originated among people who tinkered with software and still radiates out from there. Besides
column7: the author is not really qualified to write about learning other kinds.)

column1: tarot.fortuneteller.reading () () () () () (How to ask a question?) () () (Tarot only works for those who are willing to listen. These are a few guidelines that are worth following:) (You should either ask a question or make a request. Both are valid. Saying 'What does the future hold for me?' and 'Tell me about my future' are the same to the Tarot. Also
column2: avoid giving the Tarot reader unnecessary details.) (Avoid questions that have a yes/no answer. It is a limiting question because there are only two possible answers: yes
column3: or no.) (Avoid questions starting in the 'Will I…'format... For example
column4: it is best not to ask questions like 'Will I get a raise?' or 'Will I get married?' As the answers to these questions depend entirely on you.) (Keep your options open. And avoid asking close-ended questions that have limited answers. Also try not to bring in a time-element in your questions.) (Asking a question is not as accurate as making a request. The request format eliminates preconceived notions about the outcome of the reading
column5: and results in a reading that is more insightful and helpful.) () (Close)

column2: इससे आपको कोई ‌दिक्कत नहीं होगी। हनीमून की जगह और बुकिंग समय से पहले तय कर लें अन्यथा आपका मजा खराब हो सकता है। जाने से पहले सभी चीजों को खासका टिकट और बुकिंग की जगह फोन करके कंफॉर्म कर लें। जिस जगह आप जा रहे हैं
column3: वहां आप कहां-कहां धूम सकते हैं
column4: वहां की फेवरेट जगह कहां है
column5: जैसी बातों की पूरी जानकारी पहले ही ले लें। अपने पार्टनर को सहज करने के लिए साथ में सफर तय करने के लिए कुछ ऐसी चीजें जैसे कैमरा
column6: आईपॉड
column7: अच्छे गानों का सलेक्शयन और गेम्स इत्यादि साथ में रखें। इन छोटी-छोटी चीजों से आपका समय भी अच्छा गुजरेगा और आपके पल और अधिक रोमांटिक होंगे। हमेशा अपने पार्टनर के साथ रहें और उनका ख्याल रखें। कभी उन्हें अकेला ना छोड़े। अपने पास अपने बजट के हिसाब से रूपए रखें अन्यथा आपका हनीमून किरकिरा हो सकता है। अपने पार्टनर को सहज महसूस करवाने के लिए उससे बातचीत करें
column8: उसके बारे में अधिक से अधिक जानने और अपने बारे में बताने की कोशिश करें। संभव हो तो ऐसा सफर के दौरान ही कर लें
column9: इससे आप अपनी हनीमून की जगह पर पहुंच कर काफी घुल-मिल चुके होंगे। रोमांस के लिए जरूरी है फीलिंग होना और पार्टनर को समझना। इसीलिए किसी भी तरह की जल्दबाजी ना करें और पार्टनर को अपनी ओर आकर्षित करने का प्रयास करें।  संभव हो तो आप पहल ना करें बल्कि ऐसा माहौल बनाएं कि आपका पार्टनर रोमांस की पहल करें। बेहद उत्साहित होकर कुछ गलत ना बोलें लेकिन धीरे-धीरे फ्रेंडली व्यवहार करते हुए पार्टनर को भावनात्मक रूप से अपने करीब लाएं और पार्टनर का विश्वास अर्जित करें। अपने पार्टनर के साथ अपने हर पल को एन्जॉय करें
column10: ऐसे में किसी बात को लेकर गुस्सा ना हो ना ही झगड़े। बल्कि पार्टनर की मनोस्थिति को समझे और चीजों को प्यार से ट्रीट करें। जरूरी नहीं कि आप हर समय रोमांस ही करते रहें बल्कि अपने पार्टनर को जिस जगह आप गए हैं
column11: वहां पर उसका अपना स्पेस भी दें और उसे एन्जॉय करने का पूरा मौका दें। अपनी मनमानी ना चलाएं बल्कि पार्टनर की भी सुनें। बजाय इसके ‌कोई निर्णय अकेले लें अपने पार्टनर की पसंद-नापसंद भी पूछें। पार्टनर कोई ऐसी बात या व्यवहार ना करें जो आपके पार्टनर को ना सिर्फ खराब करें बल्कि आपके हनीमून को हैप्पी बनाने के बजाय अनहैप्पी बना सकता है। हेल्दी हनीमून के लिए प्रीकॉशंस जरूर बरतें। बिना प्रीकॉशंस के आप या आपका पार्टनर तनाव में आ सकता है। हनीमून के दौरान जरूरी सामान जैसे दवाईयां

column2: coarse and ovate
column3: with the lower ones being heart-shaped. They are woolly underneath. The leafstalks are generally hollow. Arctium species generally flower from July through to October. The prickly heads of these plants (burrs) are noted for easily catching on to fur and clothing (being the inspiration for Velcro)
column4: thus providing an excellent mechanism for seed dispersal. Burrs cause local irritation and can possibly cause intestinal hairballs in pets. However
column5: most animals avoid ingesting these plants. Birds are especially prone to becoming entangled with their feathers in the burrs leading to a slow death
column6: as they are unable to free themselves. A large number of species have been placed in genus Arctium at one time or another
column7: but most of them are now classified in the related genus Cousinia. The precise limits between Arctium and Cousinia are hard to define; there is an exact correlation between their molecular phylogeny. The burdocks are sometimes confused with the cockleburs (genus Xanthium) and rhubarb (genus Rheum). The roots of burdock
column8: among other plants
column9: are eaten by the larva of the Ghost Moth (Hepialus humuli). The plant is used as a food plant by other  Lepidoptera including Brown-tail

column11: Coleophora peribenanderi

column14: above-ground portions may cause contact dermatitis in humans due to the lactones the plant produces.) (Usage:) (Burdock is a perennial whose roots
column15: leaves
column16: and sometimes its seeds are used widely in herbal medicine to support liver function and as a cleansing botanical. Like dandelion and yellow dock
column17: burdock roots are bitter and thus capable of stimulating digestive secretions and aiding digestion. These roots are referred to as "alterative" agents -- capable of enhancing digestion and the absorption of nutrients and supporting the elimination of wastes. Any botanical capable of these important actions can attain far-reaching improvements in a variety of complaints. Burdock seeds and roots may be useful in treating a variety of skin conditions

column3: ” which assists with tropical interference.  New product helps track tropical cyclones'Potential tropical cyclones' numbered equally with depressions  This new product enables advisories
column4: watches and warnings for tropical disturbances that pose a threat for tropical storm or hurricane conditions to a land mass within 48 hours.  Starting this year
column5: these tropical systems are in advisory products and numbered equally with depressions. For example
column6: a Tropical Cyclone 3 can become Tropical Depression 3 or skip directly to a tropical storm if it’s the same system that has strengthened.  People in the areas that may be affected should start paying extra attention to the movement and strength of the system and have their personal preparations ready.  This new change makes it possible to get preparations underway earlier than waiting for the storm to fully form.) () () (Weather Blog: Despite recent rain

column18: 4:34 PM) (We are almost out of the dry season and heading toward the all-important wet season here in Florida.  Central Florida heading into wet weather seasonSeason last usually from late May to mid-October Location of Bermuda High can determine where storms will be   The season usually begins in late May and lasts through the middle part of October. The key players are the "Bermuda High
column19:
along with the high heat and humidity — the very things that make it somewhat uncomfortable outside during the summer but keep our landscaping green and thriving.  The Bermuda High is named for the region in which it usually stays for the summer months. It does wobble a bit, and that's where meteorology comes in.  Depending on its location, we can predict where the west and east coast sea breezes will meet and spark up heavy showers and storms. The high heat over the land causes the air to rise and be replaced by the sea breeze on both coasts.  If the prevailing winds are out of the east, then the collision will be over the western half of the peninsula. If they are south, the collision will be down the middle of the state. It is these days of 40 to 50 percent chance of showers and storms that amount to the majority of our annual rainfall.  So if your yard is brown and crunchy, don’t despair — the wet season is almost here, but it will take awhile to recover from the deficit we are in now. ) () () (Weather Blog: Several records set in April across Central Florida) (May 23, 4:14 PM) (April was yet another month with warmer and drier weather than normal. We now have a severe or moderate drought index across Central Florida. We set quite a few records. Let’s start with the records:  Orlando  April 3 had a record warm low of 71 degrees. The previous record was 69 degrees set in 1980.April 5 had a record high of 96 degrees. The previous record was 91 degrees set in 1999.   Melbourne  April 3 had a record warm low of 76 degrees. The previous record was 71 degrees set in 1960.April 4 tied a record warm low of 71 degrees set in 1974.April 5 had a record high of 92 degrees. The previous record was 91 degrees set in 1977.April 10 tied a record warm low of 71 degrees set in 1953.April 15 had a record warm low of 74 degrees. The previous record was 73 degrees set in 2015.April 16 had a record warm low of 73 degrees. The previous record was 72 degrees set in 2011.April 19 tied a record warm low of 74 degrees set in 1989.April 21 tied a record warm low of 73 degrees set in 2006.April 24 tied record high of 92 degrees set in 1963.April 28 had a record warm low of 76 degrees. The previous record was 74 degrees set in 2013.April 29 had a record warm low of 78 degrees, which was the all-time record warm low for the site in the month of April. The previous record was 74 degrees set in 2003.April 30 had a record warm low of 76 degrees. The previous record was 73 degrees set in 2012.   Daytona Beach  April 3 had a record warm low of 70 degrees. The previous record was 69 degrees set in 1929.April 5 had a record high of 91 degrees. The previous record was 90 degrees set in 1957.April 29 had a record warm low of 74 degrees. The previous record was 73 degrees set in 1991.April 30 had a record warm low of 75 degrees, which is the all-time record warm low for the site in the month of April. The previous record was 72 degrees set in 1991.Here are the average temperatures:Orlando had a monthly average temperature of 74.4 degrees, which was 3.2 degrees above normal. This ties 2006, 2002 and 1912 as the ninth warmest April on record for this site.Daytona Beach had a monthly average temperature of 71.9 degrees, which was 3.0 degrees above normal.Melbourne had a monthly average temperature of 76.0 degrees, which was 5.6 degrees above normal. This ranks as the second warmest April on record for this site.   April rainfall  Orlando had a trace of rain for the month, which was 2.68 inches below normal. This ranked as the second driest April on record for the site.Daytona Beach had 1.22 inches of rain for the month, which was 0.96 inches below normal.Melbourne had 0.23 inches of rain for the month, which was 1.90 inches below normal. This ranks as the fifth driest April on record for the site.Clermont had 0.30 inches of rain for the month, which ranks as the seventh driest April on record for the site.Sanford had 0.51 inches of rain for the month, which ranks as the sixth driest April on record for the site. ) () () (WEATHER BLOG: Central Florida saw warmer, drier March than normal) () () (Weather Blog: Saturn moon has active water, researchers say)

column1: com.app.tastycookingrecipes () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () () (0:00) () () () () (Mutton Pepper Fry Recipe | Easy Delicious Mutton Recipe | Masala Trails) () () () () () () (Watch Chef Sneha Nair make the lip smacking Mutton Pepper Fry only on Get Curried.   Mutton Pepper Fry is straight out of the foodie heartland of Kerala
column2: it is your perfect weekend menu booster
column3: whether you have a house party at your place or just a relax-on-your-couch sort of a weekend. A short trip to the nearest spice store
column4: an appetite for the hot & spicy is all you need to make most out of this lip smacking recipe!   Ingredients To Grind: Batch 1- 1 Cinnamon piece 2 Cardamom pods Few cloves  Batch 2- Few black peppercorns 500g mutton 1 tbsp coriander powder 1 tsp chilli powder 1/4 tsp turmeric powder 20 garlic pods
column5: chopped finely 6-7 slit green chillies  Some curry leaves 2 1/2 large onions
column6: chopped Salt as per taste Water as required Coconut oil for cooking  Method: - In a small tadka pan dry roast the cinnamon
column7: cardamom and cloves. Crush them with a pestle & mortar and your dry spice mix is ready. - In a pan
column8: add boneless mutton
column9: coriander powder
column10: chilli powder
column11: turmeric powder & salt. Combine this mixture well.  - Add some water and the dry spice mix to the mutton
column12: cover and let the mutton cook for 20 to 30 minutes. - In another pan
column14: chopped garlic
column15: green chillies
column17: chopped onions and a little salt.  - While the onions cook
column18: add the remaining dry spice mix and crushed black peppercorns.  - When the onions are translucent and start to brown
column19: add the cooked mutton into the pan. - Fold in the mutton with the onions & keep stirring till everything gets mixed properly. - With the pan on high flame
column20: keep stirring the mutton mixture for a few seconds and your Mutton Pepper Fry is ready be served! column1: univers.nushkhe.chaheraaa () () () () () () () () (गोरी त्वचा के लिए सरल घरेलू उपचार) () () ( गोरी त्वचा के लिए सरल घरेलू उपचार  आज के समय में हर कोई सुंदर और गोरा दिखना चाहता है।   इसके लिए वे तरह-तरह के सौंदर्य प्रसाधनों का इस्तेमाल करते हैं।   यहां पर कुछ प्राकृतिक सौंदर्य प्रसाधनों के बारे में उल्लेख किया गया है जिनके प्रयोग से चेहरे को गोरा बनाया जा सकता है।    विभिन्न औषधियों से उपचार-  1. नींबू : सुबह उठने के बाद चेहरे पर कच्चे दूध को मल लें और थोड़ा सूख जाने के बाद खाने वाले नमक को चेहरे पर लगाकर रगड़ लें।   इससे चेहरे पर जमी मैल और फालतू त्वचा बाहर निकल जायेगी।   इसके बाद नींबू और शहद को मिलाकर पूरे चेहरे पर लगायें और सूखने के बाद हल्के गर्म पानी से चेहरे को धों लें।   ऐसा करने से चेहरे का रंग निखर जाता है।   काले पैरों और हाथों पर नींबू का रस मलाई में मिलाकर रोजाना लगाने से सांवली त्वचा गोरी होने लगती है।   नींबू और टमाटर का रस बराबर मात्रा में मिलाकर चेहरे पर लगा लें और आधें घंटे के बाद चेहरे को धो लें।   इसको लगाने से चेहरे पर एक नयी ताजगी महसूस होती है।    2. जौ : 1 मुट्ठी छने हुए जौ के आटे को एक पतले से कपड़े में बांधकर पोटली बना लें।   इस पोटली को कच्चे दूध में भिगोकर हफ्ते में कम से कम 3 बार नहाते समय शरीर पर रगड़ने से धीरे-धीरे त्वचा का सांवलापन दूर हो जाता है।    3. चिरौंजी : 2 चम्मच दूध में आधा चम्मच चिरौंजी को भिगोकर लेप बनाकर चेहरे पर लगाएं और 15 मिनट के बाद चेहरे को धो लें।   यह क्रिया लगातार 45 दिनों तक करने से चेहरे का रंग निखर जाता है और चेहरे की चमक बढ़ जाती है।   इसको लगाने से रूखी और सूखी त्वचा भी कोमल हो जाती है।    4. टमाटर : 1 कच्चे टमाटर का रस निकालकर उसमें 1 बड़ा चम्मच छाछ मिला लें।   इसे रोजाना चेहरे और हाथ-पैरों की त्वचा पर लगायें और आधे घंटे के बाद धो लें।   ऐसा लगातार करने से त्वचा का सांवलापन दूर हो जाता है।    5. खीरा : 2 चम्मच खीरे के रस में आधा चम्मच नींबू का रस और चुटकी भर हल्दी मिला लें।   इसे आधे घंटे तक चेहरे पर लगाने के बाद चेहरे को पानी से धोने से चेहरे का रंग गोरा हो जाता है।    6. आलू : आंखों के नीचें के काले घेरों को हटाने के लिये आलू की 2 फांकों को काटकर उन्हे दोनों आंखों के नीचे रखकर आंख बन्द कर लें और 15 मिनट के लिये सो जायें।   इसका प्रयोग मेंकअप करने से पहले करने से आंखों के नीचे के काले घेरे मेंकअप में दिखेंगे नहीं।   आलू को पीसकर त्वचा पर मलने से त्वचा का रंग गोरा हो जाता है।    7. हल्दी : column2: Rechild What is new: -v2.2.1B216 resize widget  -v2.2.0B215 remove 'menu'and 'check' button apply new UI  -v2.1.3B213 Roll back to old widget size  -v2.1.2B212 Fix "cannot get process issue" for Android 5.0 and later version Fix widget icon. Change UI to old version.  *New feature*  1. What is the 'Check' button? This is used to check if your phone has any issues. Since this is a new feature
column3: we don't have many checking items yet. You can use it to check if your phone has any apps pushing ads.  *General help*  1. How to use it (for new users to quick start)? It is pretty simple. Open this tool and take a look at the running applications list? Uncheck some apps you don't want to kill (such as Advanced Task Killer and some system apps) Tap the button 'Kill selected apps'
column4: it will kill all applications checked.  2. How to use it (for new users to do more)? If you don't want to kill any application
column5: you can tap it on the running applications list. Then it's checking box will turn to gray.      3. Why there are programs running that I haven't used or even opened? Some applications will start up once you turn on your phone or be invoked by some events.  4. What is ignore list/ignore? Ignore list is for you to ignore some applications you don't want to kill. If you long press on the application listed on the main screen of ATK
column6: the menu will pop up
column7: then you can select 'Ignore'
column8: the application would be moved to ignore list. When you tap 'Kill selected apps'
column9: it won't be killed any more.  5. What is default action for long press You can set your default action for long press and click on the settings. The system default action for long press is pop-menu. That means you when you long press on the application(displays on the running applications list)
column10: a pop-menu would shows up. For example
column11: if you want to switch to the application after you long press on it
column12: you can set the default action of long press to 'Switch to'.   6. What is Auto-Kill We don't suggest people use auto kill. Abusing auto kill might consume more resources. If you want to kill apps automatically you need to choose one of auto-kill level 1. Safe: Only kill the apps aren't running but still consume memory. 2. Aggressive: Kill the apps running background and apps aren't running. 3. Crazy: All apps except for apps you are using with. You should be able to see Auto Kill information shows on the title
column13: like 'Auto-Kill: 12:20'. That means auto kill will start at 12:20
column14: you can also change the frequency to impact the auto kill start time. If you encounter any issues in security level low
column15: you can kill them one by one to find out which one cuase these issues
column16: then you can uncheck or ignore it.  7. What is Security Level We suggest people keep it as 'High'. Changing security level might cause some issues
column17: if you don't know your phone well.  You can set it to low to show more apps
column18: but you need know more about the apps to decide which one you need to ignore.   8. Why I have some green items on running list? Those apps are services and front apps. They cannot be killed directly in Android 2.2 and later version. You can Long Press on it and choose 'Force Stop' on the menu to force stop them. For Android 2.2 users
column19: we suggest you go to settings to ignore them if they don't consume resources very much. )

column5: and creature cards revealed this way onto the battlefield. All of these cards enter the battlefield at the same time. 	5) Each player puts all enchantment cards revealed this way onto the battlefield. An Aura put onto the battlefield this way can enchant an artifact

column7: Maryland

column9: London.  •	Studied at the Culinary Institute of Gothenburg
column10: Sweden  •	Apprenticed in Switzerland
column11: France and New York  •	Recipient of multiple James Beard Foundation Awards
column12: including Rising Star Chef and Best Chef New York City  •	Received a three-star review at age 24 from the New York Times for Aquavit
column13: making him the youngest recipient  •	Crowned champion on “Top Chef Masters” and “Chopped All Stars.” Served as a mentor on ABC’s “The Taste” and a judge on “Chopped Junior.”  •	Planned and executed President Barack Obama’s first state dinner for the prime minister of India  •	Co-produced and launched Harlem EatUp!
column14: a four-day annual festival celebrating the diversity of the neighborhood  •	Owns Red Rooster Harlem
column15: Ginny’s Supper Club and Streetbird Rotisserie (all in Harlem) and other restaurants such as American Table Brasserie and Bar in Stockholm
column17: and Marcus’ Bermuda in Hamilton
column18: Bermuda  •	Author of “Make it Messy” (Delacorte Books
column19: 2015); “Marcus Off Duty: The Recipes I Cook at Home” (Rux Martin Houghton Mifflin
column21: Chef

column24: 2009); “The Soul of a Cuisine” (Houghton Mifflin Harcourt
column25: 2006) and “Aquavit” (Rux Martin
column27: 2003).     # # #    The Power of Food   For Marcus Samuelsson
column28: food tells a story. It speaks to a time and place
column29: reflecting the soul of a community.    He sees this in Harlem
column30: an African-American enclave in the New York borough of Manhattan that rose to prominence in the '20s and later fell on economic hardship.    “I’ve always been intrigued by it
column31: ” Samuelsson says of Harlem. “But I had to ask myself
column32: what can I add to this landscape
column33: and do I have anything to say?”  Samuelsson
column34: a native of Ethiopia who was adopted and raised in Sweden
column35: arrived in New York to apprentice at Aquavit
column36: a contemporary Swedish restaurant. In short order
column37: he earned the top job
column38: and at 24 became the youngest executive chef to garner a three-star review from the New York Times.  He appreciated the Aquavit clientele and the restaurant’s well-heeled Midtown surroundings. But none of it resonated in a truly meaningful way.   The desire to connect and to be a part of something bigger than himself drew him to Harlem. After work
column39: Samuelsson would head uptown to eat (Sylvia’s is a favorite)
column40: check out the nightclubs
column41: listen to jazz and be a part of the community that gave rise to the Harlem Renaissance. This intellectual and cultural movement of African-American writers
column42: poets
column43: artists and musicians flourished in the '20s through the mid-'30s
column44: producing some of the world’s greatest writers
column45: from Langston Hughes to W.E.B. DuBois.   Samuelsson made Harlem his home 15 years ago but it took seven of them to answer his question of whether he could contribute to the culinary landscape. He needed to wrap his head around the Harlem inspired by the past but largely ignored by the present.   In 2010 Samuelsson opened Red Rooster Harlem
column46: telling his story though American comfort food with nods to his Swedish and African roots. Two years later
column47: he started Ginny’s Supper Club downstairs from The Rooster as a musical and culinary tribute to the Harlem Renaissance. In 2015 he opened Streetbird Rotisserie
column48: a casual spot for rotisserie-style chicken and several other favorites such as mac ‘n cheese and fried chicken.  “I’ve always worked globally
column49: ” he says. “But I am also inspired by what’s around me. We cook food that speaks to the neighborhood.”  That food includes dishes like Helga’s meatballs
column50: a specialty of his grandmother's who instilled in him a love for cooking
column51: fried green tomatoes and shrimp and grits.  Samuelsson’s efforts to restore the community through food cast the local and national spotlight on Harlem. Other restaurants opened along with retailers
column52: bringing jobs but also gentrification.   In 2015
column54: an annual four-day celebration of food
column55: culture and the spirit of the community. Local eateries are given the opportunity showcase their food
column56: some of which is made by the country's most prominent culinary talents.   “We do food that shows what it means be a part of restoring a community
column57: ” Samuelsson says. “Every one has a story to tell.”) () () () () () () () () () (Recipes) () () () () () () () () () () () (Folio) () () () () ()

() () () () () () () (Terms of Use / Privacy Policy for Call and SMS Tracker) (Welcome to ‘Call and SMS Tracker' Android application. If you continue to Accept and use this application you are agreeing to comply with and be bound by the following terms and conditions of use  Once accepted
column2: the app collects Call/SMS/location information of the device in the background even when the app is not in foreground or opened. This information is collected periodically and user can view their Call/SMS/location information by using the app. You can choose to disable the collection of Call/SMS/location information by using the check box in the main view of the app. These information will *not* be published over internet unless you request for it from our server. The information will be stored securely in your mobile  WORKING OF THE APPLICATION  The app works as follows  1. Every time you receive a call/SMS or make a call or send SMS
column3: the location information of the mobile is fetched. 2. All the Call/SMS/location visited along with the time will be shown by using Google Map locally. 3. You can log in into our server and then request for your Call/SMS/location history and the server will send a GCM command and fetch the Call/SMS/locaiton history of your device. You can see your Call/SMS/location history from our website.  To be in compliance with Google Play Policy we will be showing notification in top bar whenever request for details is received and uploaded to website. Call/SMS/Location details will not be uploaded automatically it will be pulled only when user logs in to the website and request for pull. All information is stored securely in server in human unreadable format and the server and database is located in US. Users can optout any time and clear the details from server either through mobile or from website. The app cannot be used as spy app as the icon cannot be hidden and notifications cannot be disabled. Please read EULA carefully before accepting.) () () (Accept) (Decline)

Recent changes:) (release: 1.2.6 date: 2012-05-20 - Fix for ANT failing to initialize after the ANT Radio Service  update 4.0 on slower phones with Bluetooth switched off. - Support for Polar and Zephyr standard Bluetooth HR sensors. - Not BTLE Still waiting on Google to make the necessary API's --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.5 date: 2012-03-24 - Adding support framework for BlueTooth Sensors. - Beta support for Zephyr and Polar initially. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.4 date: 2012-02-25 - Fix some issues with the new pedal smoothness and torque effectiveness power data fields. - Total rework of back end logging system. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.3 date: 2012-02-02 - More debug logging support especially for calibration. - Fixed bug with Slope setting. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.2 date: 2012-01-21 - More power calibration options where the device supports them. Auto Zero control
column2: Slope setting
column3: Crank length get and set. Improved debug logging. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.1 date: 2012-01-05 - Tweaks to the Temperature sensor code. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.2.0 date: 2012-12-30 - Added support for Foot pod and Temperature sensors.   - Support for the beta pedal smoothness and torque effectiveness power data fields. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.1.1 date: 2012-08-18 - Added low level debug logging option.  Added ability to manually add a sensor and set it's ID.  Will now detect the problematic Geonaute B'TWIN speed/cadence sensor.   --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.1.0 date: 2012-08-03 - Added support for opening multiple sensors of same type designated as yours.  This is to enable IpWatts. - Added support for pedaling percentage. - Fix intermittent bad cadence value from crank torque type sensor. - Prefer no data over bad high power data in very bad reception cases. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.0.3 date: 2012-07-27 - Optimizations after some work with profiling tools.  Reduced CPU usage and hopefully improved battery usage and runtime. - turned down the logging a bit more. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.0.2 date: 2012-07-13 - Improved ANT USB support
column5: - better error messaging. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 1.0.1 date: 2012-06-27 - Rebuild to support ANT USB sticks on USB HOST mode capable devices.  I consider this feature to be beta.  Feedback greatly appreciated

Turn logging right down. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.9.2 date: 2012-06-01 - more tweaking of the average cadence and power code. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.9.1 date: 2012-05-24 - Fix more cadence averaging fixes especially with bad ANT  reception conditions. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.9.0 date: 2012-05-16 - Fix Quark Cinqo cadence average issue. - Added in ANT+ branding. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.8.1 date: 2012-04-25 - Added ability to dump raw data and decode information to a file.  --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.8.0 date: 2012-04-12 - multiple application really working IpBike with IpPeloton - rework toggle bit decode to get passing certification tests --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.7.0 date: 2012-03-31 - Added calibration for Power sensors.  Fixed SRM bug. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.6.3 date: 2012-03-22 - special release with debug logging left on. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.6.2 date: 2012-02-27 - fix issue with dialog to get OiAbout app not showing - market button correctly. --------------------------------------------------------- release: 0.6.1 date: 2012-02-17 - Tweak analytics to get sensor count - Default automatic error reporting to on - tidy up searching

com.modstudio.sword.mod.mcpe () () () () () (MOD INFO) () () () (The Elemental Swords Mod adds 9 new swords. Each sword got a unique power related to its element. One sword can cause a a tornado which will make anyone in the close proximity to be thrown up into the sky and then die. Another sword can launch mobs up into the sky like a rockets. There are a wide range of different swords and the best way to experience them is to download the mod and see for yourself.  Item IDs & Crafting Recipes  ☛ Fire Sword (700) – 2 flint & steel + 1 stick ☛ Air Sword (701) – 2 glass blocks + 1 stick ☛ Water Sword (702) – 2 water buckets + 1 stick ☛ Dirt Sword (703) – 2 moss stones + 1 stick ☛ Lava Sword (704) – 8 lava buckets + 1 fire sword ☛ Ocean Sword (705) – 8 water buckets + 1 water sword ☛ Jungle Sword (706) – 8 leaves + 1 dirt sword ☛ Storm Sword (707) – 8 iron ingots + 1 air sword ☛ Thunder Sword (708) – 1 lava sword + 8 diamonds  Elemental Swords  To activate the special power of an elemental sword hold down the bottom-right button (which appears while holding a sword) for a little while and then release it.  Fire Sword  This must be one of the more powerful swords because it releases a high-powered wave of fire which will set any living creature within a radius of 15 blocks on fire.  ) ()
